Booking / Ordering Process

  • Download the Taboo App
  • Tee Times must be paid in advance through our website or Taboo App. There are no monetary refunds, a credit will be given towards a future round. No walk-up tee times will be allowed.
  • Tee time intervals are 8 minutes.
  • All Food and Beverage orders will be take-out only, and ordered online through the Taboo App.
  • Hours of Operation for the Proshop and Food and Beverage are 7:00am to 7:00pm daily.
  • Last Food and Beverage order of the day must be placed by 6:45pm.
  • Rental clubs are now available. Feeâ€™s will apply.

Arrival

  • Guests may only arrive up to 40 minutes before tee time and must complete the COVID-19 Self Declaration Form prior to arrival.
  • Social Distancing â€“ While on property, always allow for a minimum of 6ft between individuals. Signage will be installed throughout the property to help you maintain a safe distance between you and other guests.
  • Limited number of guests will be allowed in the Pro Shop at one time. Please follow all directional signage when entering the Pro Shop.
  • Guests MUST wear face protection while inside the Pro Shop.
  • The Pro Shop & on course washrooms will be open.
  • Bag drop is not available; please load your bag onto your cart. All players will be required to handle their own clubs from arrival to departure.
  • Singles and twosomes will be paired up to create foursomes.
  • NO outside alcohol is permitted on property, including the parking lot. Individuals failing to abide by this policy will be asked to leave the property immediately.

On Course

  • The Driving Range and Practice facility are open. Only 3 groups, or maximum 12 players allowed at a time. You will be invited to use the practice facility only 30 minutes prior to your scheduled tee time.
  • Scorecards will be available on your carts, scorecard is also available virtually â€“ please download and use the Taboo App.
  • Two Guests while on carts who are not members of the same household must wear a mask. If you wish to utilize a divider you are free to do so, but that does not supersede the requirement for 2 members of different households riding in a cart together from having to wear a mask.

Summer of Endless Adventure

Official Rules

  1. The Summer of Endless Adventure Sweepstakes (“Contest”) begins on July 14, 2018 at [12:00 AM] [Eastern Time and ends on August 31, 2018, at [12:00 AM] [Eastern Time] (the “Contest Period”). By participating in this Contest, you are signifying your agreement that you have read and agree to be legally bound by these Official Contest Rules (the “Rules”).
  2. To enter and to be eligible to win, entrant must be a legal resident of Ontario and must have reached the legal age of majority in Ontario. Despite the foregoing, employees, representatives or agents (and those with whom such persons are living, whether related or not) of Gulfbeck Developments Inc. (the “Contest Sponsor”), its parent organization, subsidiaries, affiliates, prize suppliers, advertising/promotion agencies and any other entity involved in the development, production, administration, or fulfilment of the Contest (collectively, the “Contest Parties”) are ineligible to enter or win.
  3. NO PURCHASE NECESSARY. To enter the Contest, the participant must visit the Gulfbeck Developments Inc. Office at 6382 Regional Road 25, Milton, Ontario L9T 2X5 (the “Sales Centre”) and follow the on-screen instructions to obtain the Official Contest Entry Form (the “Entry Form”). Fully complete the Entry Form with all required information. Once you have fully completed the Entry Form with all required information, follow the on-screen instructions to submit your completed Entry Form (each, an “Entry”). To be eligible, your Entry must be submitted and received in accordance with these Rules during the Contest Period (as determined by the Contest Sponsor in its sole and absolute discretion).
  4. There is a limit of one [1] entry per person. If it is discovered by the Contest Sponsor (using any evidence or other information made available to or otherwise discovered by the Contest Sponsor) that any person has attempted to: (i) exceed any of the limits stated in these Rules; and/or (ii) use multiple names, identities, email addresses and/or any automated, macro, script, robotic or other system(s) or program(s) to enter or otherwise participate in or to disrupt this Contest; then he/she may be disqualified from the Contest in the sole and absolute discretion of the Contest Sponsor. Your Entry may be rejected if (in the sole and absolute discretion of the Contest Sponsor) it is not fully completed with all required information and submitted and received in accordance with these Rules during the Contest Period. The Released Parties (defined below) are not responsible for late, lost, misdirected, delayed, incomplete, illegible or incompatible Entries (all of which are void). All entrants and Entries are subject to verification at any time and for any reason. The Contest Sponsor reserves the right, in its sole and absolute discretion, to require proof of identity and/or eligibility (in a form acceptable to the Contest Sponsor – including, without limitation, government issued photo identification): (i) for the purposes of verifying an individual’s eligibility to participate in this Contest; (ii) for the purposes of verifying the eligibility and/or legitimacy of any Entry or other information entered (or purportedly entered) for the purposes of this Contest; and/or (iii) for any other reason the Contest Sponsor deems necessary, in its sole and absolute discretion, for the purposes of administering this Contest in accordance with these Rules. Failure to provide such proof to the complete satisfaction of the Contest Sponsor within the timeline specified by the Contest Sponsor may result in disqualification in the sole and absolute discretion of the Contest Sponsor. The sole determinant of the time for the purposes of this Contest will be the Contest server machine(s).
  5. Prize
    1. There is a total of one (1) prize available to be won (each a "Prize" and collectively, the "Prizes") as follows:
      1. One [1] Halton Conservation Area Family Annual Pass (ARV $117.83)
      2. One [1] Mountain Equipment Co-op ("MEC") Gift Cards (ARV $250)
      3. One [1] Mountain Equipment Co-op ("MEC") Backpack (ARV $50)
      4. Two [2] "Arbor Peaks" Baseball Caps (ARV $20)
    2. The Grand Prize has an approximate retail value of $437.83 (CDN)
  6. The Prize must be accepted as awarded. The Prize may not be sold, transferred [and is not convertible to cash. Contest Sponsor reserves the right to substitute the Prize in whole or in part in the event that all or any component of the Prize is unavailable. All characteristics and features of the Prize, except as otherwise explicitly stated above, are at the Contest Sponsor’s sole and absolute discretion. The Prize winner is solely responsible for all costs not expressly described herein.
    1. On [Tuesday, September 4, 2018] at [12:00 PM] [EST], a random draw for the Prize will take place in [Toronto, ON] from among all eligible Entries received between the start of the Contest Period and [6:00 AM] [EST] on [Saturday, July 14, 2018].] On [Tuesday, September 4, 2018] at [12:00 PM] [EST] a random draw for the Prize[s] will take place in [Toronto, Ontario] from among all eligible Entries received during the Contest Period. The odds of winning the Prize will depend on the number of eligible Entries received for the random draw in accordance with these Rules.
    2. The Contest Sponsor, acting reasonably, will attempt to contact the potential Prize winner to notify him/her that he or she may have won the Prize by telephone or email (as determined by the Contest Sponsor in its sole and absolute discretion) within ten (10) business days after the draw. In the event that the potential winner cannot be contacted within such time, he or she will be disqualified and an alternate potential winner may be drawn at the Contest Sponsor’s sole and absolute discretion. Proof of identification must be provided upon request. In order to be declared the winner, the potential winner must first correctly answer, unaided, a time limited mathematical skill testing question administered by the Contest Sponsor (which may, at the Contest Sponsor’s sole and absolute discretion, be administered via the full declaration and release form described in the following sentence).
